  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Let $(M,g)$ be a spacetime which admits a complete timelike conformal Killing vector field $K$. We prove that $(M,g)$ splits globally as a standard conformastationary spacetime with respect to $K$ if and only if $(M,g)$ is distinguishing (and, thus causally continuous). Causal but non-distinguishing spacetimes with complete stationary vector fields are also exhibited. For the proof, the recently solved 'folk problems' on smoothability of time functions (moreover, the existence of a {\em temporal} function) are used.</subfield>
